cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Development RCTs in Top Economics Journals, 2021-2025: Code and Dataset"
message: "If you use this dataset or code, please cite as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Leight
    given-names: Jessica
    affiliation: International Food Policy Research Institute (IFPRI), CGIAR
    email: J.Leight@cgiar.org
abstract: >-
  Replicable pipeline and dataset identifying randomized controlled trials in
  development economics published in twelve leading economics journals over
  2021-2025. Combines OpenAlex metadata, Crossref and Semantic Scholar
  abstract backfills, EconLit JEL codes, World Bank country classifications,
  and Anthropic Claude LLM classification. Released alongside source code,
  documentation, and replication instructions.
keywords:
  - development economics
  - randomized controlled trials
  - bibliometrics
  - economics journals
  - JEL classification
license: MIT
license-url: "LICENSE"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: 2026-05-07
references:
  - type: software
    title: OpenAlex
    repository-code: "https://api.openalex.org/"
    notes: "Article metadata for 2021-2025 publications in the twelve in-scope journals."
  - type: software
    title: Crossref REST API
    repository-code: "https://api.crossref.org/"
    notes: "Abstract backfill where OpenAlex coverage is sparse."
  - type: software
    title: Semantic Scholar Graph API
    repository-code: "https://api.semanticscholar.org/graph/v1/"
    notes: "Abstract backfill via batch endpoint."
  - type: dataset
    title: AEA JEL Classification
    url: "https://www.aeaweb.org/econlit/jelCodes.php?view=jel"
    notes: "Authoritative descriptor-to-code mapping for JEL classifications."
  - type: dataset
    title: World Bank Country Classification by Income Level
    url: "https://api.worldbank.org/v2/country?format=json"
    notes: "Low-, lower-middle-, and upper-middle-income country list."
  - type: software
    title: EconLit (via EBSCOhost)
    notes: "Licensed bibliographic database accessed via institutional library; JEL codes and abstracts."
